body.description: Kids grow fast, so they need a car seat that can keep up! With a higher weight and height capacity than most other brands, Highpoint® helps your child ride safely in a booster longer. Easily converts to a backless booster. Don’t stress the juice box spills! Safe to machine wash & dry, the removable car seat cover stays looking like-new, mile after mile. No more hand washing or waiting for it to air-dry. Just quick and easy cleanup, so you can keep moving. Mindfully-made from top to bottom, this seat has a naturally flame-retardant cover with no added FR chemicals. The sleek new design comes in plenty of colors for kiddos to choose from. Fits three across to give you extra space when piling in for family trips or carpooling to soccer practice. The lightweight design means it’s easy to move from car to car without slowing down your day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great booster seat!
reviews.reviewText: Fits perfect in the car and easy to travel with. Really like the optional high back, which is easy to install and remove. Children are comfortable and prefer this seat to others we have tried in family and friends cars. This is the booster seat for us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Good seat for extended use by daughter. She says it's comfortable. Price was ok, but safety is important at any cost. Shipping was quick.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Britax is always worth the money
reviews.reviewText: We used a Britax infant seat and stroller for years, and we were very satisfied with their safety, sturdiness, and appearance. When our now-seven-year-old was clearly tall enough and weighed enough for a booster earlier this year, we shopped around but decided to stick with Britax. She loves her purple "big kid" seat and reports it is very comfortable. It is easy to latch into our CRV and weighs very little compared to her behemoth infant seat.I would note, though, that one may be limited as to which back seat to place the booster in certain SUVs because it may block part of the driver's view (our daughter's seat has to be place directly behind the driver's seat to keep all sightlines clear).Great product. Highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Extra safety, worth the money
reviews.reviewText: Totally worth the money. Sturdy seat, I love the extra lap belt positioning, it gives that extra safety to ensure the kid is not sliding off the seat in case of impact. So far it's the only brand I found that has this incorporated in their booster seats. The alligator snaps make it easier to secure it in the car. Highly reccommend, we ended up purchasing a second one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Light weight love the lap postionjng
reviews.reviewText: Lightweight and easy to move from vehicle to vehicle. I really appreciate the lap belt positioned which most boosters don’t have. Britax is amazing and the seats hold up so well. Don’t hesitate on this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works for our 5 year old
reviews.reviewText: Having a booster that used the latch system was a must for us. This seat was very easy to install and sits fairly well in my husband's Lexus sedan and my Toyota Highlander. In the Highlander there is a bit more wiggle im the back but with the kiddo strapped in it is secure. Our 5 year old daughter can easily buckle and unbuckle herself. On occasion the shoulder strap gets twisted but she is figuring out how to correct it herself. I really like the lap belt holder as it keeps the lap strap in the correct place and she can do it herself. She says it's comfortable. We have yet to take it on a long trip but for around town it meets our needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and comfortable
reviews.reviewText: We purchased this after months of research. Our previous car seats were Dionos and it was difficult to imagine that any other car seat would be as safe. As we moved from a five point harness to a booster, it was a tough decision since many boosters are so flimsy and many do not have the latch feature. This booster not only had the latch but also had the durability we were looking for.So far, this car seat has held up for our 7 year old and she does not complain that it’s uncomfortable on long drives.It also does not slide around in the seat and the top portion is securely attached to the bottom portion. I’d say it was money well spent. I’ll update later on the longevity of this purchase.
